and puts your name on a list and you get two

00:42:47.599 --> 00:42:50.849
minutes at open mic night -- which is also
why most people don't make any money from

00:42:50.849 --> 00:42:54.890
doing stand-up comedy.
So, I quickly realized that I had to start

00:42:54.890 --> 00:42:56.599
doing some routines that weren't just about
economics.

00:42:56.599 --> 00:43:00.180
I needed something easier to do jokes about.
This was in 2004.

00:43:00.180 --> 00:43:04.089
So I started doing some jokes about the war
in Iraq that I thought would appeal to people

00:43:04.089 --> 00:43:09.279
across the political spectrum.
So I'll do those for you now, and we'll see

00:43:09.279 --> 00:43:13.369
whether you still like them.
The challenge with those jokes is that it's

00:43:13.369 --> 00:43:15.609
really hard to find a political spectrum in
America.

00:43:15.609 --> 00:43:17.940
Like, everywhere you go is either far left
or far right or whatever.

00:43:17.940 --> 00:43:22.649
So, with your permission -- and this is the
audience participation part of the afternoon

00:43:22.649 --> 00:43:24.930
 -- I'm going to divide you up across the
political spectrum.

00:43:24.930 --> 00:43:28.769
So you folks over here on my left -- just
for the next couple of minutes -- I need you

00:43:28.769 --> 00:43:33.150
guys to participate.
You guys are going to be my left wing. [laughter]

00:43:33.150 --> 00:43:39.400
That was actually an appropriate amount of
enthusiasm for the left wing. [laughter]

00:43:39.400 --> 00:43:43.040
Watch this -- you folks over here to my right
 -- all you folks over here, I need you to

00:43:43.040 --> 00:43:44.400
participate.
You guys get to be my right wing.

00:43:44.400 --> 00:43:45.599
&gt;&gt; [half-hearted cheering]

00:43:45.599 --> 00:43:50.749
Yoram Bauman: That was good, but I need you
guys to dig down and find your inner red meat

00:43:50.749 --> 00:43:53.499
okay? [laughter]
Put yourselves in the mind frame of people

00:43:53.499 --> 00:43:59.829
who believe in social Darwinism.
[laughter and clapping]

00:43:59.829 --> 00:44:07.249
Put yourselves in the mind frame of people
who believe in social Darwinism, but don't

00:44:07.249 --> 00:44:11.449
believe in Darwin's theory of evolution. [laughter]
You guys over here. You guys are my right

00:44:11.449 --> 00:44:12.449
wing.

00:44:12.449 --> 00:44:13.449
&gt;&gt; [sparse cheering]

00:44:13.449 --> 00:44:16.529
Yoram Bauman: That was a little better, but
when I did this in Texas last month, they

00:44:16.529 --> 00:44:20.539
started chanting "USA." [laughter]
I want you to do that for me. You guys are

00:44:20.539 --> 00:44:21.539
my right wing!

00:44:21.539 --> 00:44:23.400
&gt;&gt; [chanting] USA! USA!

00:44:23.400 --> 00:44:28.209
Yoram Bauman: That was okay.
You guys on the left wing, though -- you guys

00:44:28.209 --> 00:44:32.319
are perfect. [laughter]
Because while the right wing was chanting

00:44:32.319 --> 00:44:36.380
"USA," you were just sitting there looking
befuddled and vaguely unpatriotic. [laughter]

00:44:36.380 --> 00:44:39.979
Don't know how it happens to the left wing;
it always does.

00:44:39.979 --> 00:44:44.080
I haven't forgotten about you people.
You all are the most important part of the

00:44:44.080 --> 00:44:49.199
political spectrum.
You're the swing voters. Your job is to be

00:44:49.199 --> 00:44:54.240
clueless and apathetic.
And then, every four years, you determine

00:44:54.240 --> 00:44:59.259
the fate of the free world. [laughter]
I know it sounds like a big responsibility,

00:44:59.259 --> 00:45:06.739
but don't give it a second thought. [laughter]
You guys are like the idiot savants of democracy.

00:45:06.739 --> 00:45:10.650
Of course, the most amusing parts of the political
spectrum are the far extremes.

00:45:10.650 --> 00:45:14.319
So the far right of the political spectrum
 -- you folks over there by the cafe and stuff

00:45:14.319 --> 00:45:21.380
 -- you guys get to be my libertarians.
That's cool. You can do what you want. [laughter]

00:45:21.380 --> 00:45:24.359
Far left of the political spectrum, on this
wall over here -- far left -- you guys get

00:45:24.359 --> 00:45:33.489
to be my libertarians. [laughter]
Did you swing voters get that joke?

00:45:33.489 --> 00:45:39.630
Libertarians. They're not the people that
check books out for you. [laughter]

00:45:39.630 --> 00:45:42.969
Libertarians are freedom lovers. All right?
They come in two flavors, right?

00:45:42.969 --> 00:45:47.969
There are right wing libertarians -- they
want everyone to be free to have guns.

00:45:47.969 --> 00:45:54.199
Left wing libertarians -- they want everyone
to be free to have drugs. [laughter]

00:45:54.199 --> 00:45:59.680
Both wings of the libertarian party want to
abolish Social Security.

00:45:59.680 --> 00:46:04.089
Right -- which makes total sense, because
who's going to make it to 65? [laughter]

00:46:04.089 --> 00:46:05.089
&gt;&gt; [Applause]

00:46:05.089 --> 00:46:10.140
Yoram Bauman: -- when the world is full of
pistol-packing pot heads.

00:46:10.140 --> 00:46:16.859
All right.
I promised you some jokes about the war that'll

00:46:16.859 --> 00:46:19.359
appeal to people across the political spectrum.
So let me start with this.

00:46:19.359 --> 00:46:21.099
I'm going to do these jokes at West Point
next week.

00:46:21.099 --> 00:46:24.130
So I'm going to try them out on you.
I don't care how you feel about the war.

00:46:24.130 --> 00:46:26.579
I don't care how you feel about President
Bush or President Obama.

00:46:26.579 --> 00:46:28.880
I think the individual troops over there deserve
our support.

00:46:28.880 --> 00:46:30.280
So I hope you join me in a round of applause.

00:46:30.280 --> 00:46:32.309
&gt;&gt; [Applause]

00:46:32.309 --> 00:46:40.230
Yoram Bauman: Nice work, left wing.
I can't believe I have to give a disclaimer

00:46:40.230 --> 00:46:43.299
before asking for a round of applause for
the troops, but the political situation in

00:46:43.299 --> 00:46:46.579
this country, ladies and gentlemen, has become
so divisive.

00:46:46.579 --> 00:46:51.059
I experienced that divisiveness firsthand
a few years ago when I moved from liberal

00:46:51.059 --> 00:46:56.029
Seattle to conservative eastern Washington
with a bumper sticker on my car.

00:46:56.029 --> 00:47:00.631
I brought a copy to show you here.
The bumper sticker said, "Bring the Troops

00:47:00.631 --> 00:47:05.279
Home."
Not a big deal in Seattle, right?

00:47:05.279 --> 00:47:11.979
But after getting my butt kicked multiple
times outside of Barnaby's pub in Walla Walla,

00:47:11.979 --> 00:47:15.299
I decided I needed to do something different
to fit in, right?

00:47:15.299 --> 00:47:19.339
So I traded in that bumper sticker.
I got a new bumper sticker that said, "Leave

00:47:19.339 --> 00:47:32.630
the Troops There." [laughter]
That one didn't work either.

00:47:32.630 --> 00:47:36.260
So then I went for something neutral, right?
I got a bumper sticker that said, "I don't

00:47:36.260 --> 00:47:42.569
know about the troops." [laughter]
Yes, I am selling these bumper stickers.

00:47:42.569 --> 00:47:47.640
And can I just say, this is going much better
than when I did this routine in Texas last

00:47:47.640 --> 00:47:50.219
month?
Because when I did this routine in Texas,

00:47:50.219 --> 00:47:53.869
this great big dude jumped up in the back.
And he was like, "That is the most offensive

00:47:53.869 --> 00:47:58.269
bumper sticker I've ever seen!" [laughter]
Well, maybe I've been hanging out with economists

00:47:58.269 --> 00:48:05.289
too long or something, but I took that as
a challenge.

00:48:05.289 --> 00:48:08.809
I looked at him, and I said, "You think that's
the most offensive bumper sticker you've ever

00:48:08.809 --> 00:48:11.059
seen?"
And I reached into my bag, and I said, "Apparently,

00:48:11.059 --> 00:48:13.749
you haven't seen this one."
It says, "If the troops weren't all in Iraq,

00:48:13.749 --> 00:48:24.200
I'd shoot one myself." [laughter]
Now, "This!" I said, "This is an offensive

00:48:24.200 --> 00:48:28.449
bumper sticker."
This guy in Texas, ladies and gentlemen -- you

00:48:28.449 --> 00:48:33.289
should have seen the look on his face.
I mean, I knew that I had won the argument

00:48:33.289 --> 00:48:37.009
about which was the more offensive bumper
sticker.

00:48:37.009 --> 00:48:40.849
What I didn't know was that he was going to
be an incredibly sore loser. [laughter]

00:48:40.849 --> 00:48:45.789
Apparently what I thought of as my rights
under the First Amendment were in conflict

00:48:45.789 --> 00:48:49.950
with what he thought of as his rights under
the Second Amendment. [laughter]

00:48:49.950 --> 00:48:52.599
But I don't back down, people.
So when this guy asked me if I was selling

00:48:52.599 --> 00:48:56.729
this bumper sticker too, I said "Heck, yes.
How many would you like to buy?"

00:48:56.729 --> 00:49:00.411
He flipped out. He jumped up on the stage.
He ripped the bumper sticker out of my hand.

00:49:00.411 --> 00:49:04.090
He got right up in my face.
He said, "I would never buy that bumper sticker

00:49:04.090 --> 00:49:08.559
and put it on my car."
And I said, "You dummy, you're not supposed

00:49:08.559 --> 00:49:12.190
to put it on your own car." [laughter]

00:49:12.190 --> 00:49:14.549
&gt;&gt; [Applause]

00:49:14.549 --> 00:49:22.209
Yoram Bauman: It's got instructions right
on the back.

00:49:22.209 --> 00:49:31.789
Step 1 -- Locate Hummer.
Step 2 -- Place over gas tank.

00:49:31.789 --> 00:49:36.469
Step 3 -- Run.
Sometimes people doubt my patriotism when

00:49:36.469 --> 00:49:38.880
I do that routine.
So let me be clear about my point, right?

00:49:38.880 --> 00:49:42.709
If you're driving a Humvee around Baghdad,
I want to thank you for the sacrifices that

00:49:42.709 --> 00:49:46.180
you're making for our country.
If you're driving a Humvee around the Bay

00:49:46.180 --> 00:49:51.469
Area, I want to put my foot up your ass.
I mean, I totally support the troops.

00:49:51.469 --> 00:49:55.439
I have extra respect for the troops, because
I'd be such a terrible fit for the military.

00:49:55.439 --> 00:49:59.890
No -- I mean, look at my arms. [laughter]
I'm like human veal.

00:49:59.890 --> 00:50:05.390
If I went to boot camp, I'd be afraid the
drill sergeant would tell me to drop and give

00:50:05.390 --> 00:50:08.209
him five push-ups.
And, as far as the military is concerned,

00:50:08.209 --> 00:50:16.160
I only have one thing going for me.
I'm not openly homosexual.

00:50:16.160 --> 00:50:18.951
But if they reinstate the draft, ladies and
gentlemen, that is going to change.

00:50:18.951 --> 00:50:27.719
It is going to change in a snap. [laughter]
It's not just me, though, because that's the

00:50:27.719 --> 00:50:30.949
military's policy, right?
If you're "out," you can't get "in."

00:50:30.949 --> 00:50:36.459
You can't even get by if you're "bi."
So if they reinstate the draft, gay is going

00:50:36.459 --> 00:50:40.519
to be the new Canada. [laughter]
Thanks a lot, everybody.

00:50:40.519 --> 00:50:41.519
Have a good rest of the day.

00:50:41.519 --> 00:50:41.759
&gt;&gt; [Applause]

